history.content: In some lower division CS classes, a small number of discussion (and lab sections in the 61 series) are held aside for CS Scholars program participants. You can identify them precisely because the enrollment limits for those sections are significantly lower than for other sections.  The section won't end up to be only 2 people but students not in CS Scholars (who are not already enrolled in those sections) will not be able to be added to that section.  You will need to pick another discussion section for CS70 -- one which has an enrollment limit of 30 or above.

I'm an EECS freshman who signed up for CS70. I wanted to sign up for discussion section 103 (WF 11-12) but I found that it had a maximum class size of 2 (while every other discussion section had a class size of 32). Is this a problem with tele bears and schedule builder or is there actually a discussion section with only 2 people in it? The CCN for section 103 was 26319.
history.subject: CS 70 Discussion 103 class size
